See %TWIKIWEB%.TWikiForms for information about Form Definitions.
Problems could arrise for two reasons:
---++ 1. Form definition missing
<ul>
  <li> [[%SCRIPTURLPATH%/view%SCRIPTSUFFIX%/%WEB%/%TOPIC%?raw=on][View raw topic text]]</li>
  <li> There should be a line that includes =META:FORM=, look for name="&lt;formName&gt;"
  <ul>
    <li> If this line isn't present see _upgrade_ section below</li>
  </ul>
  <li> There should be a topic &lt;formName&gt;</li>
  <li> If this is missing create it, otherwise check it for errors</li>
</ul>
---++ 2. Topic can not be upgraded from old style category table
This requires the form definition to be present.
This can be automatically upgraded by:
<ul>
  <li> Creating a suitable Form Definition topic
  <li> Adding a =WEBFORMS= variable in WebPreferences
</ul>

